Jaya

Jaya is a small class-based scripting language with its own compiler, CLI,
standard library, and documentation site.

Project layout:
- `jpl`: root launcher
- `src/jpl.lua`: compiler, runtime helpers, CLI, and test runner
- `src/std/`: Jaya standard library and prelude
- `tests/`: language/compiler test suites

Common commands:
- `./jpl`
  Start the Jaya REPL.
- `./jpl file.jpl`
  Compile and run a Jaya file.
- `./jpl --i file.jpl`
  Start the REPL and preload a file into the session.
- `./jpl --t`
  Run all discovered Jaya tests.
- `./jpl --t path/to/file.jpl.t`
  Run one Jaya test file.
- `./jpl --lua file.jpl`
  Print generated Lua.
- `./jpl --luac file.jpl`
  Write compiled Lua bytecode to `luac.out`.
- `./jpl --luac file.jpl output.luac`
  Write compiled Lua bytecode to a chosen output path.
- `./jpl --ast file.jpl`
  Print the parsed AST.
